
[1]fornication

   FORNICA'TION, n. [L. fornicatio.]

   1. The incontinence or lewdness of unmarried persons, male or female;
   also, the criminal conversation of a married man with an unmarried
   woman.

   2. Adultery. Matt. 5.

   3. Incest. 1Cor. 5.

   4. Idolatry; a forsaking of the true God, and worshipping of idols.
   2Chron. 21. Rev. 19.
